reviewText: Another item I bought for a friend of mine from Fiji. He took back to the Islands for his whole family to watch and they just loved it !!

I bought this video so I can learn more about Elvis Presley and his Graceland.  It is really interesting video because it has a lot of information about Graceland.  It gives quite a bit of detail information.  In this video, it has complete tour of the Graceland, and all other stuffs.  The video also show the warehouse where they store all of Elvis Presely personal belongings such as wallet with picture of his driver licence inside. The warehouse also includes his furnitures, clothings, shoes, etc.  It was fun to watch.  I would watch it over and over again.  It came from Goodwill Discount Books.  It arrived very quickly than I expected;however the DVD case broken when it arrived.  The DVD itself is okay, and able to play it okay.  I just bought a new DVD case to store them.  The overall the product was very good, interesting, and fun.
Purchased this for my mom who is a huge Elvis fan.  She loved it and said, after all these years, she still learned a few things she didn't know about him.
Yes it was good but not like being there.
Just what I was looking For.
Elvis Presly's Grsceland reached all my expectations. Iam very happy with the DVD.
great show to see where elvis lived

This is not a replacement for touring the real thing, but is a good introduction and may satisfy curiosity for the casually interested or substitute for those fans who are unable to make the journey to Memphis.  Personally, I've been there, but use the DVD to introduce my students to the varied aspects of American culture represented in this unique museum.  The extensions are limitless.
Since I cannot afford to go to Graceland, this DVD tour of Graceland is the next best thing. There are a lot of things I did not know about Graceland in this DVD. I loved it.
